description:
## Problem

`server/routes/recording.js` uses `sleep(5000)` with one retry to wait for the transcript to be available before running the call summarizer. If Twilio RT transcript delivery is delayed by >6 seconds (network hiccup, Render cold-start), summarization is silently skipped with just a `console.warn`.

Current code (lines 55-60):
```js
let transcript = await getTranscript(call.id);
if (!transcript || transcript.length < MIN_TRANSCRIPT_LENGTH) {
  console.log(`Call ${call.id}: transcript not ready, retrying in 5s...`);
  await sleep(5000);
  transcript = await getTranscript(call.id);
}
```

## Fix

Trigger summarization from the transcription route when transcript is "complete" (e.g., after Twilio's `transcription-stopped` status callback) rather than racing against the recording webhook. The recording webhook should only save the recording URL — summarization becomes a separate concern.

